<p>state below.  Allotted to messes &amp; issued with lifebelts which we either have to wear or carry about during the day &amp; use as a pillow at night.  Slept on deck, conditions practically unbearable below.  When we retired we were still at anchor waiting to put to sea.</p>
<p>Sunday 18/6/16<br/>Put to sea at 10 AM.  Owing to number of troops on board, the meals are carried out in three sittings.  Sea very calm; paraded with life belts 10 AM.  Alarm blew at 3.30 pm.</p>
